g.text: Spring Mattress: There's a greasy old spring mattress in the corner, resting on piles of softcover books. White linen and a pillow are visible under a worn-out karakul blanket.
You: Maybe a little shut-eye, just for an hour... [Go to sleep.]
"Maybe a little shut-eye, just an hour..." [Go to sleep.]
Esprit de Corps: You don't have to be a hero.
Cuno: "Cool, whatever. Cuno doesn't really give a shit."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The offer still stands," he says, looking out the pillbox window. "Take it -- you don't look so good."
Pain Threshold: A flash of pain interrupts you, making you wince instead of letting the words out.
You: "There are signs that someone... lives..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You know, officer..." He looks at you with a touch of concern. "You *can* rest here if you're feeling tired. I will keep watch. You could use some rest for what's ahead."
You: "There are signs that someone... lives..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. Any time. If you need a rest *later*, it's okay by me."
Endurance: Technically speaking, you *could* rest here if you're hurting... someone else has. It should be possible.
Pain Threshold: You force the rest of the sentence out through pain, thick as molasses, no longer able to hear yourself speak.
Endurance: Still rather inviting, all things considered. It's much warmer inside than out there...
You: Curl up with your knees close to your chest.
Spring Mattress: The blanket feels cold. The entire room does -- concrete and cold. Minutes pass. Half an hour maybe? The sounds of the sea beyond grow distant. Your eyelids close. Until...
Spring Mattress: The greasy old spring mattress lies in the corner, fresh linen under the heavy karakul cover.
Endurance: You didn't realize how tired you were. Your body is still nowhere near healed...
You: "Do you think whoever slept here is..."
Inland Empire: Also -- what if the bad thing happens again?
Spring Mattress: Maybe it's actually better on the mainland... in your own bed. This place is getting less welcoming.
Cuno: "Check this shit. Someone's been squatting here." The kid waves his hand at the bed. "Cuno knows because this shit looks like Cuno's place."
Spring Mattress: You feel yourself standing up in the darkness. Right next to the mattress. Slowly, the world begins to hatch from the blackness. It's evening...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Someone has been squatting here." The lieutenant inspects the bed. "The linen is fresh. Recently washed."
Logic: Someone has been squatting here. Very recently -- the fire guy the twins mentioned?
Pain Threshold: You push the rest of the thought through pain thick as molasses, without really concentrating on it.
You: "Do you think whoever slept here is..."
Cuno: "I'm gonna say it again -- Cuno doesn't feel like carrying your corpse off this island, so maybe you should fucking crash?"
Pain Threshold: You force the rest of the sentence out through pain, thick as molasses, without really hearing it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe it's better to get back to the mainland? Rest there -- you've earned it."
Cuno: "Hey... Cuno doesn't wanna *hurt your feelings*, but you look like shit. Maybe you should lie down in the bed -- like recover. Before you die."
Cuno: "What, you wanna like... live on this fucking island now?" He crosses his arms. "Go sleep in your own bed."
Spring Mattress: The blanket feels cold. It's someone else's blanket, and the room is all concrete and cold. Sounds of the sea beyond grow distant, slowly. Your eyelids close.
Endurance: The bed is quite inviting, all things considered. It's much warmer inside than out there...
Spring Mattress: It stands out because it's freshly washed.
You: Curl up with your knees close to your chest.
Spring Mattress: You face the concrete wall. There's less light there, in the dark corner. Like a dog you lie there...
Spring Mattress: You face the concrete wall. There's less light there, in the dark corner. Like a dog you lie there...
Pain Threshold: A flash of pain interrupts you, making you grimace instead of spewing out the words.
Endurance: You didn't realize how tired you were. Your body is still nowhere near healed...
You: No time to rest now. [Leave.]
Logic: Someone has been squatting here. Very recently.
Spring Mattress: The greasy old spring mattress lies in the corner.
Pain Threshold: A flash of pain interrupts your thought, making you grimace.
You: Pull your legs under your chin.
You: Curl up with your knees close to your chest.
Inland Empire: The mattress is soggy, but that linen feels more inviting than the pain and exhaustion. It's not too cold here...
